This paper discusses adversarial training, which is a popular topic in machine learning and computer security. The paper proposes a novel variant of adversarial training, which is a technique used in deep learning, and evaluates its effectiveness against various types of attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of intermediate versions of the models, which is related to optimization and search algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for evaluating the robustness of the models, which is related to performance evaluation, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
